name: intelligent-transportation-systems-research-data-exchange-safety-pilot-model-deployment-on-cbb38
notes: The main objectives of the Safety Pilot Model Deployment (SPMD) include the exploration of the real-world effectiveness of connected vehicle safety applications in multi-modal driving conditions, the evaluation of how drivers adapted to the use of this connected vehicle technology, and the identification of potential safety benefits as a result of this connected vehicle technology. The SPMD - One Day Sample data environment contains sanitized mobility data elements that were collected from over 2700 vehicles, equipped with connected vehicle technologies, traversing Ann Arbor, MI. The data included in this data environment were generated on April 11, 2013. The mobility data provided in this environment is intended to support continued advancements in the connected vehicle domain as well as the development of applications to support improved transportation operation.
